land Season 6 [Blu-ray] [2017]|publisher=Amazon.co.uk|accessdate=January 6, 2018}}</ref>\n| {{Start date|2017|7|19}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ezydvd.com.au/blu-ray/Homeland-Season-6/dp/6204288|title=Homeland: Season 6|publisher=EzyDVD|accessdate=January 6, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Homeland (season 7)|7]]\n| 12\n| {{Start date|2019|8|13}} (DVD only)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.amazon.com/dp/B07DY286QX/ |title=Homeland Season 7 |publisher=Amazon.com |access-date=July 18, 2019}}</ref>\n| {{Start date|2018|9|24}}<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.amazon.co.uk/dp/B07D7M91VN|title=Homeland Season 7 [Blu-ray] [2018]|publisher=Amazon.co.uk|accessdate=November 2, 2019}}</ref>\n| {{Start date|2018|11|5}} (DVD only)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.jbhifi.com.au/products/homeland-season-7-2017-dvd |title=Homeland - Season 7 |publisher=JB Hi-Fi |access-date=November 2, 2019}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Broadcast==\nInternationally, the series premiered on November 1, 2011, on [[Super Channel (Canada)|Super Channel]] in Canada,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.channelcanada.com/canadian-channels/pay-tv-channels/super-channel/claire-danes-stars-in-homeland-a-new-series-by-the-producers-of-24-and-dexter-only-on-super-channel|title=Claire Danes stars in Homeland, a new series by the producers of 24 and Dexter \u2013 Only on Super Channel|work=Channel Canada|date=October 4, 2011|accessdate=June 4, 2013}}</ref> on January 13, 2012, on [[Raidi\u00f3 Teilif\u00eds \u00c9ireann|RT\u00c9]] in Ireland,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rte.ie/ten/blogs/2011/1231/434605-homeland/|title=Five Dramas for 2012|work=RT\u00c9 Ten|date=December 31, 2011|accessdate=January 10, 2012}}</ref> on January 22, 2012, on [[Network Ten]] in Australia,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.popsugar.com.au/Homeland-TV-Preview-Starring-Claire-Danes-Damian-Lewis-Network-Ten-21416285|title=TV Preview: Homeland Starring Claire Danes|work=Pop Sugar|date=January 20, 2012|accessdate=January 11, 2014}}</ref> on February 19, 2012, on [[Channel 4]] in the United Kingdom,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.channel4.com/programmes/homeland|title=Homeland \u2013 Channel 4|work=[[Channel 4]]|accessdate=February 9, 2012}}</ref> and on September 30, 2013, on [[Star World]] in [[Bangladesh]], [[India]] and [[Pakistan]].<ref>{{cite web|title=First episode of Homeland season 3 to premiere exclusively on the Star World Premiere website |url=http://www.indiantelevision.com/release/y2k13/sep/seprel130.php |publisher=IndianTelevision.com |date=September 27, 2013 |accessdate=October 1, 2013}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{sisterlinks|display=''Homeland''|d=Q23594|n=no|b=no|v=no|voy=no|s=no|wikt=no|c=Category:Homeland (TV series)|m=no|mw=no|species=no}}\n* {{Official website}}\n* {{IMDb title|1796960|Homeland}}\n* {{tv.com show|homeland-2011|Homeland}}\n* [http://www.emmys.com/shows/homeland ''Homeland''] at Emmys.com\n\n{{Homeland episodes|state=expanded}}\n{{Navboxes\n|title = [[List of awards and nominations received by Homeland|Awards for ''Homeland'']]\n|list =\n{{CriticsChoiceTVBestDramaSeries}}\n{{EmmyAward DramaSeries 2001\u20132025}}\n{{GoldenGlobeTVDrama 2010\u20132029}}\n{{Producers Guild of America Award for Best Episodic Drama}}\n{{Satellite Award Best Drama Television Series}}\n{{TCA Award for Outstanding New Program}}\n{{WritersGuildofAmericaEpisodicDramaScreenplay}}\n{{Writers Guild of America Award for Television: New Series}}\n}}\n{{Showtime Network programming}}\n\n[[Category:2011 American television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2010s American crime drama television series]]\n[[Category:2010s American political television series]]\n[[Category:2020s American crime drama television series]]\n[[Category:2020s American political television series]]\n[[Category:American television series based on Israeli television series]]\n[[Category:Best Drama Series Golden Globe winners]]\n[[Category:Bipolar disorder in fiction]]\n[[Category:Central Intelligence Agency in fiction]]\n[[Category:Crime thriller television series]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Espionage television series]]\n[[Category:Homeland (TV series)| ]]\n[[Category:Islam in fiction]]\n[[Category:American military television series]]\n[[Category:Peabody Award-winning television programs]]\n[[Category:Prisoners of war in popular culture]]\n[[Category:Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Drama Series winners]]\n[[Category:Primetime Emmy Award-winning television series]]\n[[Category:Serial drama television series]]\n[[Category:Showtime (TV network) original programming]]\n[[Category:Russian Foreign Intelligence Service in fiction]]\n[[Category:Suspense television series]]\n[[Category:Television series by 20th Century Fox Television]]\n[[Category:Television shows filmed in North Carolina]]\n[[Category:Television shows set in Virginia]]\n[[Category:Television shows set in Washington, D.C.]]\n[[Category:Television shows set in Pakistan]]\n[[Category:Television shows set in New York City]]\n[[Category:Terrorism in television]]\n[[Category:Television shows set in Berlin]]\n[[Category:Television programs about the United States Marine Corps]]\n[[Category:American political drama television series]]\n[[Category:American spy thriller television series]]\n", "text_old": "{{Short description|American political thriller television series}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name = Homeland\n| image = HomelandTVSeries.jpg\n| caption = \n| genre = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Serial (radio and television)|Serial drama]]\n* [[Spy fiction|Espionage thriller]]\n* [[Psychological thriller]]\n* [[Political thriller]]\n}}\n| based_on = {{based_on|''[[Prisoners of War (TV series)|Prisoners of War]]''|[[Gideon Raff]]}}\n| developer = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Howard Gordon]]\n* [[Alex Gansa]]\n}}\n| starring = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Claire Danes]]\n* [[Damian Lewis]]\n* [[Morena Baccarin]]\n* [[David Harewood]]\n* [[Diego Klattenhoff]]\n* [[Jackson Pace]]\n* [[Morgan Saylor]]\n